❤️ HEARTSYNC – IoT Based Real-Time Heart Monitoring System
🚀 Overview

HEARTSYNC is an IoT-based real-time heart monitoring system designed to capture live heart rate data using a sensor module and Arduino, and display the readings dynamically on a web dashboard using Firebase.

The system enables remote health monitoring by synchronizing physiological data to a cloud database and presenting it through a user-friendly web interface.

🧠 Problem Statement

Continuous heart monitoring systems are often expensive or limited to hospital environments.

HEARTSYNC aims to create a low-cost, real-time heart rate monitoring solution using accessible hardware and cloud integration.

💡 Solution

The system integrates:

🫀 Heart rate sensor module

🔌 Arduino microcontroller

☁ Firebase Realtime Database

🌐 Web dashboard for live monitoring

It captures heart rate signals, processes them via Arduino, sends structured data to Firebase, and reflects live updates on the web interface.

